This paper deals with representation learning methods for healthcare data, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and healthcare. The paper specifically focuses on using graph-based representation learning methods on a healthcare knowledge graph, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also involves working with large datasets and evaluating performance on various tasks, which could fall under databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
